# Step 2: Compare Green vs Amber

Filter:

```python
green = df[df["cod_band"]=="Green"]
amber = df[df["cod_band"]=="Amber"]
```

---

## Mean SHAP Shift

```python
summary = []

for feature in features:

    shap_col = f"{feature}_shap"

    green_mean = green[shap_col].mean()

    amber_mean = amber[shap_col].mean()

    shift = amber_mean - green_mean

    summary.append({
        "feature":feature,
        "green_mean_shap":green_mean,
        "amber_mean_shap":amber_mean,
        "shap_shift":shift
    })

shift_df = pd.DataFrame(summary)
```

---

## Interpretation

Suppose:

| Feature     | Green | Amber | Shift |
| ----------- | ----- | ----- | ----- |
| Utilization | 0.32  | -0.28 | -0.60 |
| Delay       | 0.12  | -0.20 | -0.32 |

The more negative the shift, the stronger the driver of deterioration.

