# Step 3: Measure Impact Category Movement

This is the most important part.

Convert categories into scores.

```python
impact_score = {
    "Strong Negative":-2,
    "Moderate Negative":-1,
    "Neutral":0,
    "Moderate Positive":1,
    "Strong Positive":2
}
```

---

## Compute Shift

```python
category_results = []

for feature in features:

    impact_col = f"{feature}_impact"

    green_score = (
        green[impact_col]
        .map(impact_score)
        .mean()
    )

    amber_score = (
        amber[impact_col]
        .map(impact_score)
        .mean()
    )

    shift = amber_score - green_score

    category_results.append({
        "feature":feature,
        "green_category_score":green_score,
        "amber_category_score":amber_score,
        "category_shift":shift
    })

category_shift_df = pd.DataFrame(category_results)
```

---

## Interpretation

| Feature     | Green Score | Amber Score | Shift |
| ----------- | ----------- | ----------- | ----- |
| Utilization | 1.5         | -1.2        | -2.7  |
| Delay       | 0.8         | -0.7        | -1.5  |

Utilization deteriorates the most.

