# Step 5: Create Amber Lift Score

This identifies categories highly associated with Amber.

```python
lift_results = []

for feature in features:

    impact_col = f"{feature}_impact"

    for category in df[impact_col].unique():

        amber_pct = (
            amber[impact_col]
            .eq(category)
            .mean()
        )

        green_pct = (
            green[impact_col]
            .eq(category)
            .mean()
        )

        lift = amber_pct / max(green_pct,0.0001)

        lift_results.append({
            "feature":feature,
            "category":category,
            "amber_pct":amber_pct,
            "green_pct":green_pct,
            "lift":lift
        })

lift_df = pd.DataFrame(lift_results)
```

---

## Interpretation

| Feature     | Category        | Lift |
| ----------- | --------------- | ---- |
| Utilization | Strong Negative | 7.2  |
| Delay       | Strong Negative | 5.1  |

Meaning:

Records with Utilization = Strong Negative SHAP are 7.2x more likely to be Amber than Green.

