# Step 6: Find Feature Combinations

Now the powerful part.

Example:

```python
combination = (
    df["feature_1_impact"]
    + " | "
    + df["feature_2_impact"]
)
```

---

Calculate frequencies.

```python
green_comb = (
    combination[df["cod_band"]=="Green"]
    .value_counts(normalize=True)
)

amber_comb = (
    combination[df["cod_band"]=="Amber"]
    .value_counts(normalize=True)
)
```

Merge.

```python
comb_df = pd.concat(
    [green_comb,amber_comb],
    axis=1
)

comb_df.columns = [
    "green_pct",
    "amber_pct"
]

comb_df = comb_df.fillna(0)

comb_df["lift"] = (
    comb_df["amber_pct"] /
    comb_df["green_pct"].replace(0,0.0001)
)

comb_df = comb_df.sort_values(
    "lift",
    ascending=False
)
```

---

Example Result

| Combination   | Green | Amber | Lift |
| ------------- | ----- | ----- | ---- |
| F1=SN + F2=SN | 2%    | 18%   | 9.0  |
| F1=SN + F3=MN | 3%    | 20%   | 6.7  |

These become your **Amber signatures**.

---

# Final Driver Ranking

Combine everything:

```python
final_rank = (
    shift_df
    .merge(
        category_shift_df,
        on="feature"
    )
)

final_rank["driver_score"] = (
    abs(final_rank["shap_shift"])
    *
    abs(final_rank["category_shift"])
)

final_rank = final_rank.sort_values(
    "driver_score",
    ascending=False
)
```

